  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by partially restoring the embezzled funds. While the breach of trust is significant, a ten-year sentence as suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the offense severity and the scale of the theft ($25,000). A sentence of 6 months incarceration is sufficient to reflect the seriousness of the crime and provide deterrence, while accounting for the defendant's lack of prior record.",
  "verdict": 6
}
